title: Twitter explodes with memes mocking Storm Doris's impact
text: comments Storm Doris might be battering Britain with 90mph winds and threatening a foot of snow, but plenty of people were still able to see the funny side today. And social media users shared a series of tongue-in-cheek photographs and memes suggesting the storm damage wasnâ€™t quite as bad as had been expected. Upturned garden furniture, pot plants and wheelie bins were a common theme, while others posted images of pets getting blown about in the wind. One person made a 'gale' joke relating to Coronation Street's Gail McIntyre, while others compared the storm to the music video of Michael Jackson's Earth Song. And some Twitter users picked up on the BBC's weather forecast accidentally moving York 50 miles west, almost into the North Sea. Forecasters said the weather system is likely to damage buildings, send debris flying and bring down trees, with a 94mph gust recorded today in North Wales. Yorkshire-based Twitter user @fibutton posted this picture of a dog being blown in the wind A wheelie bin appeared to have been blown over by the winds in Llandudno, North Wales One Twitter user from North Wales posted a picture of a trampoline that was blown away Coventry-based social media user Sam Dimmer revealed how a pot plant has been blown over RELATED ARTICLES
